                Isidi <expan><abbr>Reg</abbr><ex>inae</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>sac</abbr><ex>rum</ex></expan> <lb n="2"/>ob <expan><abbr>honor</abbr><ex>em</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>divin</abbr><ex>ae</ex></expan> <lb n="3"/>domus pro salute <lb n="4"/><expan><abbr>colon</abbr><ex>iae</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>Iul</abbr><ex>iae</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>Aug</abbr><ex>ustae</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>Philippiens</abbr><ex>ium</ex></expan> <lb n="5"/><expan><abbr>Q</abbr><ex>uintus</ex></expan> Mofius <expan><abbr>Euhemer</abbr><ex>us</ex></expan> <lb n="6"/>medicus ex imperio <lb n="7"/><expan><abbr>p</abbr><ex>ecunia</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>s</abbr><ex>ua</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>p</abbr><ex>osuit</ex></expan> idem subsel<expan><ex>l</ex><abbr>ia</abbr></expan> quattuor <lb n="8"/>loco <expan><abbr>adsig</abbr><ex>nato</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>d</abbr><ex>ecreto</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>d</abbr><ex>ecurionum</ex></expan>
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Es befinden sich zwei christliche Symbole an der rechten Seite des Steins. (B): In Z. 4 steht irrtumlicherweise col(oniae) statt colon(iae) in AE 1930.</p>
